On a relatively recent Ubuntu system you should be able to install and try out Kunquat by doing the following:

sudo -k apt-get install build-essential libwavpack-dev libpulse-dev python3 python3-pyqt5 python3-pyqt5.qtsvg check libsndfile1-dev libsamplerate0-dev
./get_build_support.sh
./make.py
./make.py --prefix=~/kunquat install
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/kunquat/lib
export PYTHONPATH=`python3 -c "import os, sys; print(os.path.expanduser('~/kunquat/lib/python{0}.{1}/site-packages'.format(*sys.version_info)))"`
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-tracker

NOTE: Kunquat is in an early development stage. Don't expect it to do anything useful.


On MacOS Sierra you might be able to install and use some parts of Kunquat by doing the following:

brew install wget python3 libsndfile wavpack pkg-config check pulseaudio libsamplerate
pip3 install pyqt5
./get_build_support.sh
./make.py --disable-threads --disable-tests
./make.py --disable-threads --disable-tests --prefix=~/kunquat install
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/kunquat/lib
export PYTHONPATH=`python3 -c "import os, sys; print(os.path.expanduser('~/kunquat/lib/python{0}.{1}/site-packages'.format(*sys.version_info)))"`
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-player
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-export
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-tracker

Follow https://github.com/kunquat/kunquat/issues/698 for ongoing macOS problem solving.
